Information
------------------------------
The silent killer in Yemen's ongoing conflict is starvation. Nawal Al-Maghafi travels to the city of Hodeida - while it is being bombed by Saudi-led forces. In this disturbing film she finds children with severe malnutrition and hospitals whose medical supplies have run out and where staff are unable to help the most desperate. She follows one of the few doctors still working in the remote areas of the region on a mission to save the hungry children of Yemen.
